    ('BUS-A 325', 'COST AND PERFORMANCE MEASUREMENT FOR DECISION MAKING', '1114', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 11:10 AM–12:25 PM', 'HH 2046', 'Jordan Bable', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'This course covers a management accounting framework for budgeting and control via cost measurement and performance evaluation. Students will learn different methods and applications for measuring and evaluating the cost and profitability of goods and services within an organization, with an emphasis on facilitating managerial decision-making.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
