    ('BUS-A 329', 'TAXES AND DECISION MAKING', '6500', 'Closed', 'MW Monday, Wednesday 2:20 PM–3:35 PM', 'HH 3030', 'Greg Geisler', 0, NULL, 'Lecture', '3', 'HODGE HALL (BUSINESS SCHOOL)', ARRAY[]::TEXT[], 'The course provides a broad understanding of the federal income tax consequences of common business and investment transactions. Students will learn the role of income taxes in evaluating individual taxpayer and business decisions, apply federal income tax laws appropriately, and differentiate financial reporting standards from federal tax law.', ARRAY['Class uses IU eTexts'], NULL),
